						<summary>

						<p>Nandi pillar (same side) in the Vīśvēvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1233, Chaitra.</hi> It may correspond to 1311 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It seems to record the remission of tolls and also mentions Tripurayadēvaya.</p>						

						</summary>
